    public interface HandlerContextAware
    An implementing object is capable of storing context that is visible to all RequestHandler2.

    This interface is subject to change and should not be implemented by users of the SDK.

      • addHandlerContext

        <X> void addHandlerContext(HandlerContextKey<X> key,
                           X value)
        Adds a context to that is visible to all RequestHandler2s. Note that, context added here will available only for the scope of the request execution and will not be marshalled over the wire.
        Parameters:
        key - the key for the property being set in the request.
        value - the value for the property being set in the request.
